WNBA 2020 Schedule After Nine Games

Source: R/data.R
wnba_2020_first_nine_games.Rd

A dataset containing the scores of the first nine games of the WNBA 2020 season, followed by the schedule for the rest of the season. This is used as a test / sample dataset for the mvglmmRank modeling and game prediction functions.

wnba_2020_first_nine_games

Format

A data frame with 132 rows and 7 variables:

date

game date

away

away team name

away.response

away team score

home

home team name

home.response

home team score

neutral.site

is the site neutral? 0=F, 1=T, all set to 0

binary.response

did the home team win? 0=F, 1=T

Source

https://www.basketball-reference.com/wnba/years/2020-schedule.html

Details

Note that all 2020 WNBA games are played in the "Wubble" in Bradenton, Florida, ostensibly a neutral site. However, each team is assigned "home" or "away" status, the game times are set so they make sense to the home team's fans, and the background sounds and advertising displays mirror those a home team viewer would hear and see. Somewhat surprisingly, the models I've run so far indicate that there is a home-court advantage!
